Kansas State Department of Education
September 9 at 9:15 PM 路

Kansas law KSA 8-1556 requires all motorists to stop when approaching or overtaking a stopped school bus displaying its flashing red lights and stop arm.

Motorists are to remain stopped until the bus is no longer displaying its flashing red lights and stop arm.

Violation of this law not only endangers children but is punishable by a fine and court costs in excess of $420.

post_text: Beginning Thursday, September 10, USD 269 will be utilizing the waiver from USDA to offer FREE Breakfast and Lunch for ALL students. Meals will be served and provided as normal; however, your childs breakfast/lunch account will NOT be charged. Meals will be served on the days USD 269 is in session. If school is cancelled due to inclement weather, no meals will be served that day. If your child currently has a positive lunch balance, the money will remain as a credit until this program ends. Please feel free to contact the school if you have any questions.

Rooks County Health Department
June 29 at 6:21 PM 路

Rooks County Update for 6/29/2020

A person who subsequently tested positive for COVID-19 attended the Palco High School graduation ceremony on Saturday, June 20. We believe the risk to other attendees is low but encourage all who attended the event to carefully monitor for fever and other signs of illness. Please notify your primary care physician or the health department if you are concerned you may also be ill or desire testing. Wearing a mask in public will help prevent further spread in pre-symptomatic individuals.

post_text:
Hey, can we get a hand with this? And maybe also a foot? :)

Today's one-minute workout will require brains AND brawn. 60 seconds of alternating partner single-leg squats will really keep you on your TOES! (...but hopefully not really on your toes. Please keep your weight in your heels, thanks.)
"Lean on me, when you're not strong
And I'll be your friend
I'll help you carry on
For it won't be long
'Til I'm gonna need
Somebody to lean on"
You just call on us, ROOSTERS, when you need a hand!
We all need somebody to lean on! :)
Share this video or YOUR version of the workout, using these hashtags #RoosterFitnessChallenge #USD269 #OneMinuteWorkout

When things get a bit difficult, always remember the BUTTERFLY! Why? The butterfly overcomes scary obstacles and spends some time alone in a cocoon before emerging, transformed...and we can do that, too! :)

"When things go wrong, as they sometimes will,
When the road you're trudging seems all uphill,
When the funds are low and the debts are high,
And you want to smile, but you have to sigh,
When care is pressing you down a bit-
Rest if you must, but don't you quit."

Roosters, your USD #269 faculty and staff LOVE and MISS you! Take our best wishes and the strength of the butterfly into this workout -- alternating butterfly kicks -- and our next few weeks of school!

post_text:
Dear USD 269 Students, Parents, and Guardians

Since news broke Tuesday of Governor Kellys decision the Kansas Department of Education (KSDE) has been working hard to provide schools direction on how best to continue educating and meeting the needs of students. We know there are questions, so we want to provide you with what we do know as of now.

March 16-20- Facilities closed by Governor Kelly
March 23-27- USD 269 scheduled Spring Break
March 30-April 3- No Students at USD 269
April 6- Continuous Learning Plan begins

The KSDE Continuous Learning Task Force has released guidance and USD 269 staff will be meeting and developing a plan specific to our students. Once plans have been finalized families will be notified. Please be patient as we work through this unprecedented time. We know that this uncertainty can be frustrating. Thank you all for your support.

It's a great day to be a Rooster! At tonight's final home game versus Heartland Christian, we will honor our 5 senior girls, recognize WKLL All-Academic Team, and honor our two WKLL scholarship-testing winners. Our junior high pep band will be playing tonight. Also, our Little Roosters will put on a performance. Finally, our NHS students will be selling fresh Krispy Kreme donuts. Here is the schedule of events for the evening:

6:00 Honoring our seniors
Girls Varsity Tip-off
WKLL All-Academic Team recognition
WKLL Scholarship testing winners recognized
Boys Varsity Tip-off
Half-time of boys varsity: Little Roosters perform

Remember, admission is free, thanks to a generous anonymous donation. Our student-athletes would love to see you cheering in the stands!

post_text:
The DES #5thGradeFam presents to you: "The Runaway City," about the lost American colony of Roanoke. Students worked hard last week, learning about the history of this mysterious colony. They also learned about special effects (SFX) and were asked to incorporate several of these into their production. Then, the class worked together in order to build a miniature landscape, on which they acted out an original Readers' Theater play. Please put your hands together for these awesome historians/filmmakers!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nwJiZ_GD4aI&feature=youtu.be
